Balinese laugh together as 5,000 Balinese people take part in a 'Laughing Yoga' event in Ubud on Indonesia Bali island. AFP/Sonny Tumbelaka UBUD - Yogis in Indonesia are taking the saying 'laughter is the best medicine' very seriously. Thousands of people gathered for a laughter yoga session on the resort island of Bali. The aim is to heal themselves with giggles and pray for world peace. Laughing yoga practitioners say it helps them cope with stress and deal with problems at home.